				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${{\rm{E}}}_{B3LYP}^{QM9-G4MP2}$$\end{document}EB3LYPQM9-G4MP2 values are smaller than the corresponding EQM9 values. This finding means that the newly found conformations in the QM9-G4MP2 set are more stable and likely closer to the global minimum than the QM9 conformations. While the index of 117523 has the largest discrepancy of ~20 kcal/mol, all other cases show 3~5 kcal/mol energy differences. The relatively small energy difference of 3~5 kcal/mol can be sufficiently induced by conformational changes alone, even without connectivity changes. The largest deviation (20 kcal/mol) is observed for the trimolecular systems, which may have many local minima due to complex intermolecular interactions, thus introducing large deviations among conformers.

